data.database_description: The database is designed to manage and track information related to a driving school business model. It includes tables for storing address details that are associated with staff members and customers, capturing personal and professional data about staff, and maintaining customer profiles along with their payment histories. Additionally, it tracks the details of vehicles used in lessons and records each lesson's specifics, including involved customers, assigned staff, vehicle usage, scheduling, and pricing. The relationships between these tables ensure comprehensive management of operations from administrative functions to service delivery.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each address entry.
Primary location detail including number and building name.
Name of the city where the address is located.
Postal code for the address location.
State, province or county information relevant to the address.
Country where the address is located.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores detailed address information for entities such as staff and customers.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each staff member.
Reference to the address of the staff member, linked to Addresses table.
Informal name or alias used for the staff member.
First name of the staff member.
Middle name of the staff member, if applicable.
Last name or surname of the staff member.
Birth date and time of the staff member.
Date and time when the staff member joined the driving school.
Date and time when the staff member left the driving school, if applicable.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains personal and professional details of staff members associated with the driving school.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each vehicle
Description or type of the vehicle (e.g., Van, Truck)

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains details about vehicles used for driving lessons.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each customer; primary key.
Identifier linking to the address of the customer; foreign key to Addresses table.
Status indicator categorizing the customer (e.g., Good Customer, Bad Customer).
Timestamp marking when the individual became a customer.
Date of birth for each customer.
First name of the customer.
Last name of the customer.
The total outstanding balance owed by the customer.
Email address associated with the customer for communication purposes.
Primary contact phone number of the customer.
Cell or mobile phone number for contacting the customer.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Contains personal and status information about customers enrolled in the driving school.

columns.columnDescription: Identifier for the customer making the payment; links to the Customers table.
Timestamp indicating when the payment was made.
Code representing the method used for payment (e.g., Direct Debit, Credit Card).
The monetary value of the payment transaction.

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Stores payment transactions made by customers, including details such as payment method and amount.

columns.columnDescription: Unique identifier for each lesson
Identifier linking to the customer taking the lesson
Status of the lesson (e.g., Completed, Cancelled)
Identifier linking to the staff member conducting the lesson
Identifier for the vehicle used during the lesson
Date and time when the lesson occurs
Duration of the lesson in hours
Cost charged for the lesson

enriched_schema.tableDescription: Tracks details of driving lessons including scheduling, involved parties, and pricing.
